    <h1>Bun's Adventure at the Beach</h1>
    
    <!-- The Story Section -->
    <h2>The Story</h2>
    <p>The sun was shining brightly as Bun arrived at the beach. He felt the warm sand under his paws and ran towards the water. Bun splashed around in the waves and barked with joy.</p>
    <p>Bun noticed a group of colorful seashells scattered along the shore. He sniffed each one, his nose twitching with curiosity. Bun picked up a particularly shiny shell and carried it in his mouth as he explored further down the beach.</p>
    <p>As Bun was exploring, he found a bottle buried in the sand. The bottle was old and had something inside. Bun carefully pushed the bottle with his nose until the cork popped off. Inside was a small, rolled-up piece of paper. Bun used his paws to gently unroll the paper, revealing a map with strange symbols and drawings.</p>
    <p>Bun tilted his head and studied the map closely. The map showed a drawing of the beach with a big X marking a spot near some rocks. Bun looked around and saw the rocks in the distance.</p>
    <p>Excited, Bun ran towards the rocks, stopping now and then to check the map. When he reached the spot marked with the X, Bun began to dig in the sand. Suddenly, his paw hit something hard. It was a small wooden box. Inside the box was a shiny golden locket. Bun nudged the locket open with his nose and found a tiny picture of the famous Admiral Pugwash, a legendary pug from Pugwash, Nova Scotia, who was famous for sailing the seven seas.</p>
    <p>After a long day, Bun was tired but happy. He lay down on the sand, the locket safely by his side, and looked at the waves. Today was the best day ever!</p>

    <!-- Vocabulary Section -->
    <h2>Vocabulary</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Shore - the land along the edge of the sea.</li>
        <li>Locket - a small piece of jewelry that opens to show a picture inside.</li>
        <li>Admiral - a high-ranking officer in the navy.</li>
        <li>Nova Scotia - a province in Canada.</li>
        <li>Twitching - moving with a small, quick motion.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Comprehension Questions Section -->
    <h2>Comprehension Questions</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>What did Bun do when he first arrived at the beach?</li>
        <li>What did Bun find along the shore?</li>
        <li>What did Bun find inside the bottle?</li>
        <li>How did Bun use the map to find the hidden treasure?</li>
        <li>Who was in the picture that Bun found in the locket?</li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Discussion Questions Section -->
    <h2>Discussion Questions</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Have you ever found something special at the beach? What was it?</li>
        <li>If you could travel to Nova Scotia, what would you like to see or do?</li>
        <li>What is your favorite thing to do at the beach?</li>
        <li>If you had a locket, whose picture would you keep inside it?</li>
        <li>Do you prefer the mountains or the beach? Why?</li>
        <li>What is the most interesting place you have ever visited?</li>
        <li>Do you enjoy swimming in the sea or in a pool? Why?</li>
        <li>What is your favorite book or movie about adventure?</li>
        <li>Have you ever collected something? What was it, and why did you collect it?</li>
        <li>Have you ever found a hidden or secret place? What was it like?</li>
        <li>What is your favorite way to explore new places?</li>
    </ol>

